th a unique and immersive experience. With AR Ricci Map, exhibition visitors can experience the maps in a new and engaging way, enhancing their understanding and appreciation of these important historical maps. For more details, please find at &lt;a href="https://library.hkust.edu.hk/china-in-maps/">https://library.hkust.edu.hk/china-in-maps/&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Vis2023invited</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vis2023invited/</link><pubDate>Wed, 30 Aug 2023 16:24:10 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vis2023invited/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Thesis</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/thesis/</link><pubDate>Wed, 30 Aug 2023 16:23:55 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/thesis/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Mm2023metashadow</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/mm2023metashadow/</link><pubDate>Wed, 26 Jul 2023 21:54:02 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/mm2023metashadow/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Augmenting Situated Visualizations with Tangible User Interfaces</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/projects/tui4vis/</link><pubDate>Sat, 22 Jul 2023 12:29:38 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/projects/tui4vis/</guid><description>&lt;p>The goal of this project is to bring data analysis into everyday life for better sensemaking in situ by introducing a better user interface for AR situated visualizations. We aim to use 3D printed objects to serve as interactive mediums in enhancing AR situated visualizations.&lt;/p>
